org.apache.flex.swc

Interface ISWCVersion

  • All Known Implementing Classes:
    SWCVersion

    public interface ISWCVersion
    Version information of a SWC file. Since Flex 3, Flex version is decoupled with SWC library version.

      • getFlexMinSupportedVersionInt

        int getFlexMinSupportedVersionInt()
        Get the flex min supported version as an integer. The bits 24-31 are the flex major version number, bits 16-23 are the flex minor version number, and bits 0-15 are the flex revision number.

        For example, "4.6.1" becomes (4<<24) | (6<<16) | 1.

        Returns:
        the flex min supported version as an integer

      • getCompilerVersion

        String getCompilerVersion()
        The version of the compiler that created the SWC. Set the version of the compiler that created the SWC. The version of the compiler has three components: 1) a major version, 2) a minor version, and 3) a nano verison. The components are separated by dots, for example "4.7.0".
        Returns:
        version of the compiler.

      • setCompilerVersion

        void setCompilerVersion(String value)
        Set the version of the compiler that created the SWC. The version of the compiler has three components: 1) a major version, 2) a minor version, and 3) a nano verison. The components are separated by dots, for example "4.7.0".
        Parameters:
        value - version of the compiler, not validated.

      • getCompilerBuild

        String getCompilerBuild()
        The build number of the compiler that created the SWC. The build number is an integer generated by the source control system used for the compiler's development, "777".
        Returns:
        build number of the compiler.

      • setCompilerBuild

        Parameters:
